cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the spectrum efficiency of wireless networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with optimizing the transmission probabilities of users to achieve maximum system throughput, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an algorithm to find the optimal transmission probabilities, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of power settings on network performance, which can be related to multimedia applications that require high bandwidth and low latency. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus, the paper briefly mentions the security implications of NOMA and how it can be addressed, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
